  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">3 Safe Water Wells for 195 rural homes in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The rural safe water supply project is intended towards saving lives of the people from the, diseased, dirty, saline, hard and corrosive water, by providing safe clean water. This bad water has in the past been the  major source of deaths due to water born diseases like; typhoid, biliharzia, cholera and dysentry. It will involve constructing, digging and installing a hand pump for 65 safe water supply wells per each in Kayunga, Kangulumira, Busaana sub counties of Kayunga District in Uganda.</narrative>
  </description>
